# ðŸŸ¨ Gold Layer Data Dictionary: Sales Data Mart

## ðŸ“˜ Overview
The Gold Layer represents the **business-ready, curated data** used for reporting and analytics. It integrates cleaned and conformed data from the Silver Layer into a **Star Schema**, optimized for performance and usability. This layer supports KPI dashboards, ad hoc analysis, and executive reporting.

The schema includes:
- **Fact Table**: `gold.fact_sales`
- **Dimension Tables**: `gold.dim_customers`, `gold.dim_products`, `gold.dim_time`

---

## ðŸ“Š Table: `gold.fact_sales`

| Column Name    | Data Type     | Description                                  | Purpose                     |
|----------------|---------------|----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| order_number   | nvarchar(50)  | Unique identifier for each sales transaction | Primary Key                 |
| product_key    | bigint        | Foreign key linking to `dim_products`        | Join with product attributes |
| customer_key   | bigint        | Foreign key linking to `dim_customers`       | Join with customer attributes |
| order_date     | date          | Date when the order was placed               | Time-based analysis         |
| shipping_date  | date          | Date when the order was shipped              | Delivery performance        |
| due_date       | date          | Date when payment is due                     | Payment tracking            |
| sales_amount   | int           | Total revenue from the sale                  | Revenue calculation         |
| quantity       | int           | Number of units sold                         | Volume tracking             |
| price          | int           | Unit price of the product                    | Pricing analysis            |

> ðŸ’¡ *Derived Metric*: `sales_amount = quantity Ã— price`

